<SLUG> BC-BKC-UCNOTE-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
WATSON KEEPS BRUINS ON GUARD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   MINNEAPOLIS _ The UCLA Bruins have enough weapons to overcome a
poor game by sharpshooting forward Jason Kapono, or hulking center
Dan Gadzuric, or gifted forward Jerome Moiso.
</P>
<P>
   However, they might not be able to survive and advance in the
NCAA Tournament without a consistent and solid effort from point
guard Earl Watson.
</P>
<P>
   In March Madness, guards rule.
</P>
<P>
   The best are calming influences. They control the tempo, they
direct the offense and they get the ball to the right players at
the right times.
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins don't want erratic guard Ray Young taking 3-pointers
in the final minutes of a close game. They want Kapono, Moiso or
JaRon Rush taking big shots. It's Watson's job to make that
happens.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have to make sure we have our rotations down and that we're
organized on offense,'' Watson said. ``I have to call the right
sets, distribute the ball and make sure the guys are in the right
position.''
</P>
<P>
   In recent weeks, he's done it all. Watson is averaging 6.2
assists and 2.7 turnovers in the last six games. UCLA won all six.
</P>
<P>
   How will he respond to tournament pressure?
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm comfortable and I'm excited,'' he said ``This is the first
time in the tournament that we've had our team together. No one's
hurt. No one's suspended.''
</P>
<P>
   Two years ago, Jelani McCoy quit in midseason and Baron Davis
was injured in the tournament. Last year, center Dan Gadzuric did
not play in the NCAAs because of a knee injury.
</P>
<P>
   __ The Knight of time: Quietly, reserve guard Billy Knight had a
remarkable late-season resurgence. He did not play a second against
the Oregon schools Feb. 24 and 26, but he charged off the bench to
make five critical 3-pointers in victories over Cal and Stanford.
</P>
<P>
   It was ideal timing for the Bruins, who might need Knight's
marksmanship in the tournament. Single-elimination pressure, zone
defenses and dome stadiums often make for difficult shooting
environments.
</P>
<P>
   ``The fact that Billy has emerged as an offensive threat and is
playing with such confidence couldn't be better,'' Bruins coach
Steve Lavin said.
</P>
<P>
   __ Defending Duane: Ball State's top scorer and best player is
guard Duane Clemens, a crafty left-hander who can penetrate or
shoot 3-pointers.
</P>
<P>
   In man-to-man situations, the Bruins probably will rotate
defenders on Clemens. It could be Watson, Young or Ryan Bailey. If
that fails, they'll switch to a matchup zone and extend it to the
3-point line.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have to do a good job keeping him out of the paint,'' said
Steve Spencer, the UCLA assistant who oversees the defense.
</P>
<P>
   Watch for Ball State to counter UCLA's size with speed, perhaps
with a three-guard attack. The combination of Clemens, point guard
Mickey Hosier and one of two reserve guards, Cedric Moodie or
Patrick Jackson, could force the Bruins to go small.
</P>
<P>
   ``They've gone with three guards sometimes,'' Spencer said.
``We'll go with our lineup, they'll go with their's, and we'll see
who adjusts. If they're going to play zone, they might go bigger.
</P>
<P>
   __ And finally: Gadzuric suffered a mild sprain of his left
thumb during practice Wednesday but expects to be ready tonight.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's nothing serious,'' he said. ``It's the same thing I did
at Syracuse.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
