<BODY>
 PM-BUDGET-NYT 
 (rk) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; For THURSDAY PMs &LR;
</P>
<P>
   Here are the top news stories from The New York Times News
Service for PMs of Thursday, March 16.
</P>
<P>
   The PMs news desk, 212-556-1927, opens at 7 a.m. Eastern Time.
To get story repeats before this hour call 212-621-1595 for reruns
on AP DataFeatures or 214-980-8305 or 8367 for repeats on UPI
DataNews.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TAIWAN-BUSINESS (Beijing) _ There are many prominent
Taiwanese businessmen and their families who live and work in
Beijing. A look at their thoughts and lives. It's an interesting
group since _ of all the divided countries _ this is the only
instance where people have lived and worked in the ``enemy camp,''
so to speak. By Elisabeth Rosenthal. 1,700 words.
</P>
<P>
