   LA-PRIVATE-PRISONS (New Orleans) _ A judge here has accused one
of the largest private prison companies in the nation, Wakenhut, of
treating inmates in a for-profit juvenile prison like animals and
has freed two teen-age boys after finding they had been brutalized
by guards, kept in solitary confinement for months for no reason
and deprived of routine things like shoes, blankets, education and
medical care. The judge said the teen-agers had been entrusted to
the prison ``for the avowed purpose of rehabilitation'' and ``these
young people deserve to be treated like human beings, not
animals.'' By Fox Butterfield. 1,500 words.
