</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-GREENE _ Review of the book ``Greene on Capri,'' by
Shirley Hazzard. Book offers a fragrant, funny, precise picture of
a writer whose considerable worldly success never tempted him into
untoward displays of optimism. (Eyman, Palm Beach Post). 21. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-COUNTRY _ Review of ``Another Country'' by Mary Pipher,
who offers ideas about how to bridge the gap between older
generations and their children and grandchildren. (Bell, Rocky
Mount Telegram). 20. MOVED
</P>
