<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0314 -- Having married a foodie, the allure of
good regional cuisine has become important to me in deciding where
to travel. That's why when visiting Washington recently, I
suggested a jaunt to the Eastern Shore of Maryland _ for the area's
top-notch crab cakes, of course. (Meyers, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes a 4-column color photo of a
crabber heading out to the bay and a 1-column color photo of a pile
of Blue Crabs
</P>
