<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-CLOSERYOUGET-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BATTLE O' THE SEXES, LOTS O' FUN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROBERT PHILPOT 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Seems like every year or so, an amusing, inconsequential
Irish-themed movie pops up _ ``The Matchmaker'' in 1997, ``Waking
Ned Devine'' in late '98/early '99. If you enjoyed those, you'll
probably enjoy ``The Closer You Get,'' which someone had the brains
to release to Middle America on St. Patrick's Day.
</P>
<P>
   This lightweight battle-of-the-sexes comedy takes place on
Ireland's Donegal coast, in a small village where everybody knows
one another, and most people are single. The men, bored with local
options, are inspired (by Bo Derek, of all people) to advertise in
the Miami Herald for American female companionship. The women
discover this, and come up with plans of their own to snag the lads
of their choice. Considering how many arrested-development cases
there are among the men, it's a wonder the women don't place an ad
of their own: ``Single Irish lasses seek lads with a bit o' sense
in 'em.''
</P>
<P>
   Naturally, the answer to the movie's key problem is right under
everyone's noses, but that doesn't mean that an hour and a half of
whimsy can't take place. Kieran (Ian Hart), the town butcher and
male ringleader, changes his appearance in hopes of snagging a
bride, not noticing the attentions of a frustrated co-worker
(Cathleen Bradley). His brother Ian (Sean McGinley) nurses a shy
crush on a local barmaid (Niamh Cusack).
</P>
<P>
   Emotions flare at a dance, men serenade women with recorded
music, people fall in love by taking quiet walks. If this sounds
familiar, it should _ it's an American teen comedy, with the
characters aged 15 years and speaking in charming brogues.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   Film: ``The Closer You Get''
</P>
<P>
   Rating: 3 on a 1-5 scale
</P>
<P>
   Length: 92 minutes
</P>
<P>
   Rated: PG-13
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Robert Philpot is film critic for the Fort Worth Star-Telegram.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) nn
</P>
</TEXT>
