<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TAKING A CLOSE LOOK AT LASIK SURGERY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I read a newspaper article about a group called Eyes for
people who have had bad experiences with Lasik eye surgery. How can
I contact this group?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.P.S., Savannah, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: It sounds like you're referring to the Surgical Eyes
Foundation, a not-for-profit New York group for people who had bad
experiences with Lasik, RK and other refractive eye surgery
techniques.
</P>
<P>
   To contact the group, write to Surgical Eyes, 341 Lafayette St.,
No. 169, New York, NY 10012; call (212) 431-5465; or visit the Web
site www.surgicaleyes.org.
</P>
<P>
   ``Surgical Eyes was founded to focus attention on the unique
problems recipients of unsuccessful refractive surgery undergo,''
the group states on its Web site. The group publishes photos
showing ``day driving haloes,'' ``ghosting'' and other vision
problems that may occur following surgery.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How do us older camera owners take flash pictures, now that
you can't find flashbulbs available in the stores anymore?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.I., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Cress Photo, a mail-order retailer that calls itself the
``world's largest flashbulb dealer,'' sells more than 60 different
bulbs.
</P>
<P>
   ``Flashbulbs have not been manufactured worldwide in many
years,'' according to the company's Web site at www.flashbulbs.com.
``The bulbs that you receive are previously manufactured stock
which has been obtained from a variety of sources.''
</P>
<P>
   Cress carries three different AG-sizes, five M-sizes, Flash
Cubes, Magi Cubes, Flash Bars, Flash 60s, Philips PF cubes and many
others. For ordering information, write to Bill Cress, Box 4262,
Wayne, NJ 07474-4262, or call (973) 694-1280.
</P>
<P>
   Q: They mentioned on ``Jeopardy!'' that the Democratic
Convention begins on Aug. 14. When does the Republican Convention
begin?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.D., N. Richland Hills, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The GOP convention will take place from July 29 to Aug. 4, in
Philadelphia, which has hosted the party's convention in 1856,
1877, 1900, 1940 and 1948. The Democratic Convention occurs Aug.
14-17 in Los Angeles, which last hosted the event in 1960.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
