<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-FESTIVALS16-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Savannah, Ga. _ The annual St. Patrick's Day parade, the
second largest in the country, winds through the historic district
from Forsyth Park to Bay Street and back on Friday. The procession
includes more than 265 groups, including 30 floats, 30 family units
and 25 bands, including the Budweiser Clydesdales, the Mummers of
Philadelphia, the Summerall Guards from The Citadel in Charleston
and those wacky Shriners. 1-877-728-2662 or www.savannah-visit.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Macon, Ga. _ The International Cherry Blossom Festival, Friday
through March 27, encompases 500 events, including a performance by
the Tommy Dorsey Orchestra and historic tours. The fest celebrates
the blossoming of nearly a quarter-million Yoshino cherry trees.
912-751-7429, www.cherryblossom.com
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Columbus, Ga. _ The Springer Opera House presents the musical
``Grease'' Thursday through April 8. Performances are 8 p.m.
Thursday-Saturday; also, March 22-25, March 30-April 1 and April
6-8 and 2:30 p.m. Sunday and March 26. 706-327-3688.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Atlanta _ Geared to Go, which specializes in outdoor gear,
rental equipment and guided trips, celebrates its move to a new
location with an open house featuring outdoors experts and
representatives of manufacturers, trail clubs, state parks, the
U.S. Forest Service, environmental and conservation groups and
other outdoor organizations and outfitters. 10 a.m.-5 p.m.
Saturday. 4313 Northeast Expressway. 678-406-0008.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pigeon Forge, Tenn. _ The sixth annual ``A Mountain
Quiltfest'' is today through Sunday at the Smoky Mountain
Convention Center. Event features quiltmaking classes and an
exhibition of one-of-a-kind quilts. 1-800-251-9100.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Birmingham _ The Birmingham Museum of Art presents ``Art in
Bloom'' Friday through Sunday. The event features 61 flower
arrangements by more than 70 local and regional floral designers
who interpret, through flowers, selected art works. Also, workshop,
lecture and demonstration by South African floral designer Charles
Kinnear. 205-254-2565 or www.artsBMA.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine, Fla. _ The play ``Conquest &AMP; Colonization,''
Thursdays and Fridays through April 14 at the St. Augustine
Amphitheater, portrays the settlement of the city in 1565 by Don
Pedro Menendez de Aviles. 904-824-9449.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Miami Beach _ Artist Carlos Betancourt and poets Richard
Blanco, Fred D'Aguiar and Campbell McGrath will present ``The
Sounds, Symbols Project,'' a 300-foot-by-90-foot art installation
and performance on the sand at 21st Street on Sunday. Inspired by
Caribbean and African tribal symbols, the 24-hour environmental art
installation will consist of thousands of individually sculpted
wood shapes anchored to the beach to outline a large-scale form
over the sand. 305-573-9955.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hickory, N.C. _ The Third Annual Catawba Vallery Pottery
Festival March 24-25 focuses on Southern traditional pottery. Along
with historical pottery on exhibit, there will be contemporary
potters selling their wares, antiques and folk art. The featured
lecturer will be Charlotte Brown, director of the Gallery of Art
and Design at North Carolina State University. Tickets for the
March 24 evening gala ($25) must be purchased by Thursday.
828-322-5890.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Orlando _ The Orlando Museum of Art presents
``Twentieth-Century Still-Life Paintings from the Phillips
Collection,'' through May 21. The nationally touring exhibition of
70 paintings by 47 artists brings together modern American and
European still-lifes. 407-896-4231 or www.OMArt.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Orlando _ Mardi Gras at Universal Studios Florida continues
through April 1. 407-363-8000 or www.uescape.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  If you have a story idea, press release or calendar listing or
want to give us feedback, write to The Atlanta
Journal-Constitution, Travel Section, 72 Marietta St. N.W.,
Atlanta, GA 30303. Or e-mail: travel(at)ajc.com
</P>
