<P>
   UNDATED _ With so few original ideas out there, some directors
are deciding that the best film route is one that crosses paths
with many genres. The Wachowski brothers did it with ``The
Matrix,'' blending science fiction, martial arts and action
inspired by Hong Kong films; David O. Russell did it with ``Three
Kings,'' merging ``The Treasure of Sierra Madre,'' ``Gunga Din''
and ``MASH'' and tossing them into a Persian Gulf War story. Now
Jim Jarmusch is doing it with ``Ghost Dog: The Way of the
Samurai,'' in which Jarmusch appears to be after the all-time
cinematic cross-pollination. By ROBERT PHILPOT. Story has moved in
``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
