<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, March 17 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, please contact Stewart Slavin at the Daily
News at (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   FILM-LOANS (Los Angeles) _ In a move that will help the film
industry, the U.S. Export Import Bank will provide independent film
producers and qualified lenders with production loan guarantees.
The action puts the film industry on par with the same kind of
financial backing available to manufacturers and producers of U.S.
goods and services for export. By Marla Matzer Rose.
</P>
<P>
   GAS-STRAIN (Los Angeles) _ Gasoline prices have jumped 27 cents
a gallon in the last month, putting a strain on the budgets of many
low hourly wage earners like restaurant delivery drivers and others
who use their cars for buisiness. by Jason Cohen.
</P>
</TEXT>
