<P>
   ASBESTOS-AGENCY (Washington) _ Davitt McAteer has spent a lot of
time agonizing about how his agency, the Mine Safety and Health
Administration, should have done more to prevent the slow, painful
deaths of hundreds of miners, processing plant workers and their
families who died of exposure to asbestos. He says he's going to
``make damn sure that it doesn't happen again.''
</P>
<P>
