Exchange Commission, said yesterday that Nasdaq's SelectNet system,
which matches orders electronically, ``continues to be plagued with
shortcomings, delays during heavy trading volume, and even
outages.'' By Floyd Norris.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
</P>
<P>
   Here are tonight's columns:
</P>
<P>
   MARKET (New York) _ Investors bought stocks furiously Thursday,
sending the Dow Jones industrial average up nearly 500 points in
its biggest one-day point gain since October 1987. Broader indexes
also rose sharply as investors _ at least for the day _ put aside
fears that the Federal Reserve will aggressively raise interest
rates and slow the economy to a crawl. By Alex Berenson.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET.)
