<P>
   VT-CIVIL-UNIONS (Montpelier, Vt.) _ After a day of impassioned
debate, the Vermont House of Representatives passed a bill that
would guarantee legal benefits to gay and lesbian couples. The
76-69 vote brings Vermont a step closer to granting more rights to
same-sex couples than any other state, although the bill stops
short of letting gay and lesbian couples legally marry. By Carey
Goldberg. (We plan to move the story by 9 p.m. ET in ``a'' news
file.)
</P>
