<P>
   NJ-SPRAWL (Hopewell, N.J.) _ Gov. Christine Todd Whitman has
said that she would make New Jersey a national model for
controlling growth in ways that protect open space and serve the
cities. But as the most recent census figures once again show,
talking about sprawl is easier than limiting it, particularly in
the boom times of Central New Jersey. By Iver Peterson. (The story
has moved in ``a'' news file.) 1,900 words.
