<P>
   NASA-METEOR (Houston) _ Scientists at the Johnson Space Center
have begun studies of meteor fragments that fell in western Canada
earlier this year. What is unusual about the fragments is that they
fell in ice, were quickly found and were frozen. Experts believe
they have essentially been frozen for 4.5 billion years, the age of
the solar system, potentially preserving a record of pre-life
chemistry. By MARK CARREAU.
