<P>
   (NYT46) NEW YORK -- March 16, 2000 -- NY-POLICE-SHOOTING --
Patrick M. Dorismond, an unarmed Brooklyn man, was killed outside
the Wakamba Cocktail Lounge in Manhattan early Thursday during a
scuffle with detectives, the authorities said. The details of the
shooting were sketchy and there were conflicting accounts of the
episode, but a senior investigator and a man who saw the scuffle
said Dorismond, 26, who worked as a security guard, was angered
when one of the undercover detectives approached him and asked to
buy drugs. (Keith Meyers/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT45) NEW YORK -- March 16, 2000 -- THOMAS-PROFILE -- ``The
Vagina Monologues'' has made room for Marlo Thomas. For the last
two weeks, Thomas has been displaying her crimson pedicure and,
with two other barefoot divas, Rita Moreno and Cynthia Nixon,
clambered aboard a bar stool inside the Westside Theater to share a
90-minute reverie about a body part that would have made her blush
back in her ``That Girl'' heyday. Not anymore. ``It's not anything
you look through other glasses to understand,'' she says. ``Every
woman in the place is laughing, crying, gasping.'' (Frances
Roberts/The New York Times)
</P>
