was a landmark survey of its subject, and a revelation. Now comes
``Souls Grown Deep,'' the book. Sure to be a landmark as well, the
hefty tome is the first of at least three predicted volumes.
William L. Hawkins' enamel on masonite ``Girl in Red Dress With
Cats and Dogs'' (1985) is one of the works included in the book.
