<P>
   (NYT39) WASHINGTON -- March 16, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN., MARCH 19
-- BOOKS-SOULS-1-COX -- ``Souls Grown Deep,'' the 1996 Olympics
exhibition of art by Southern African-American self-taught artists,
was a landmark survey of its subject. Now comes ``Souls Grown
Deep,'' the book. Sure to be a landmark as well, the hefty tome is
the first of at least three predicted volumes. Rep. John Lewis,
D-Ga., who contributed an essay, sees the connection between the
civil rights movement and the flowering of this art as part of
``this whole desire to be liberated, not just from physical
barriers but being free of spirit and free of mind.'' (Rick
McKay/Cox News Service)
