the U.S. One tier is made up of doctors who take insurance, the
other offers doctors with time and attention to give but take only
cash. Dr. Herbert Rubin, a gastroenterologist, in his office next
to signs warning patients that he does not accept insurance.
(Edward Carreon/The New York Times)
