customers help each other with knitting projects. Only now the
quips are being printed in Time magazine and Entertainment Weekly,
and they're about how many people -- young and old, male and
female, famous and infamous -- can't get their fill of this ``knit
one, purl two'' stuff. (David Sprague/The Los Angeles Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) STUDIO CITY, Calif. -- March 16, 2000 --
KNITTING-CELEBS-1-LADN -- Actress Daryl Hannah knits a scarf at La
Knitterie Parisienne. Once considered the nerdiest, most old
ladyish of crafts, knitting is the butt of jokes once again. Only
now the quips are being printed in Time magazine and Entertainment
Weekly, and they're about how many people -- young and old, male
and female, famous and infamous -- can't get their fill of this
``knit one, purl two'' stuff. (David Sprague/The Los Angeles Daily
News) LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NY8) GAINESVILLE, Fla. -- March 16, 2000 -- FL-GIRL-KIDNAPPED-2
