<HEADLINE>
UTAH STATE UNHAPPY WITH SEED
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOHNNY PAUL, WENDELL BARNHOUSE AND MIKE JONES 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The NCAA selection committee placed Utah State in the South
Region and awarded the Aggies a No. 12 seed, ``which has stirred up
a lot of conversation,'' coach Stu Morrill said.
</P>
<P>
   ``That is not something we can focus on, but it is something our
conference needs to address,'' Morrill said.
</P>
<P>
   The Aggies enter the NCAA Tournament with the nation's longest
winning streak at 19 and were ranked 27th nationally in RPI.
Connecticut coach Jim Calhoun expected the Aggies to be seeded
ninth or 10th, but ``they're not, and we're playing them.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Coach Calhoun was nice enough to say that he was not happy to
have to play us,'' Morrill said. ``I can turn that around and say,
`How do you think I feel?' ''
</P>
<P>
   Yet, the Big West Conference's regular-season and tournament
champions can find solace in the fact that at least one No. 12 seed
has won its first-round game during the past 11 NCAA Tournaments.
STRANGE YEAR FOR 'HEELS
</P>
<P>
   North Carolina (18-13) finished the season unranked in The
Associated Press Poll.
</P>
<P>
   It marked the eighth consecutive week that the Tar Heels were
not ranked after spending 172 consecutive weeks in the AP poll, the
second-longest streak in NCAA history. ``I think we were a little
overrated in preseason, but it's the head coach's job to get the
most out of the team,'' Tar Heels coach Bill Guthridge said, ``and
we have not been clicking on all cylinders this season.'' DO YOU
KNOW US?
</P>
<P>
   The University of Louisiana at Lafayette appears to be suffering
from an identity crisis.
</P>
<P>
   Formerly known as the University of Southwestern Louisiana, it
became the University of Louisiana at Lafayette on Sept. 10. Their
postseason media guide makes that rather clear.
</P>
<P>
   ``With the new name change, please refer to us as
Louisiana-Lafayette, UL Lafayette, Louisiana's Ragin' Cajuns,
Ragin' Cajuns or Cajuns,'' the media guide requests. ``Please do
not use `ULL' or abbreviate Lafayette in any references.''
</P>
<P>
   Duly noted. BENCH STRENGTH
</P>
<P>
   The Ragin' Cajuns' Orlando Butler leads Louisiana-Lafayette in
scoring at 13.1 points per game, but the junior guard has not
started a game this season for coach Jessie Evans.
</P>
<P>
   ``My role on this team is to feed off the starting five,''
Butler said. ``(Not) starting doesn't bother me,'' Butler said.
``Starting is just another thing I don't have to worry about.''
DELAYED START
</P>
<P>
   The Kentucky-St. Bonaventure double-overtime game was the first
game of the afternoon session at the Midwest Region site in
Cleveland. That meant the second game between Syracuse and Stamford
started nearly 45 minutes later than expected.
</P>
<P>
   ``We were very anxious, we wanted to get out there and play,''
Syracuse senior guard Jason Hart said of the wait in the locker
room. ``The more I sat there, the more butterflies I accumulated in
my stomach.''
</P>
<P>
   Syracuse coach Jim Boeheim said he thinks his team lost a little
bit of its edge.
</P>
<P>
   ``I actually left the locker room and watched some of the
(Kentucky-St. Bonaventure) game,'' he said. ``The toughest thing in
coaching is having to wait for the game.''
</P>
<P>
   Samford fell behind 24-13 in the game's first 10 minutes, but
Bulldogs coach Jimmy Tillette did not blame the game's delayed
start for his team's 79-65 loss.
</P>
<P>
   ``I feel like I did not have these guys prepared well enough and
the late start had nothing to do with the result,'' he said. QUE
SERA
</P>
<P>
   Indiana State players were philosophical about their
opening-round loss to Texas in the program's first tournament
experience in 21 years.
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought we had a great season,'' forward Matt Renn said.
``Getting 20 wins and making it to the NCAA Tournament was our goal
and we accomplished that. Hopefully, this will become a standard at
Indiana State.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
