<SLUG> BC-CHRISCRAFT-UPN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
CHRIS-CRAFT LOSES UPN RULING, BOOSTING VIACOM IN CBS BID 
</HEADLINE>
   (bl)  
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A state Supreme Court justice has upheld an ultimatum
that Chris-Craft Industries has to buy or sell its interest in the
fledgling UPN network by Monday, giving Viacom Inc. a big victory
in its quest to complete its merger with CBS Corp.
</P>
<P>
   UPN, which was started five years ago, is a 50-50 partnership
between Viacom and Chris-Craft.
</P>
<P>
   Justice Herman Cahn ruled Thursday against all of Chris-Craft's
motions to thwart a buy-sell provision initiated by Viacom and CBS.
</P>
<P>
   The provision would force Chris-Craft to sell its interest in
UPN for $5 million, meaning it would gain no value for the asset it
has tried to build up for the last five years or else buy the
network for the same figure, and assume all future losses by the
network. To date UPN has lost about $800 million.
</P>
<P>
   Though Chris-Craft does have the right to appeal to the state
appellate division, one executive involved in the legal action said
that even an appeal would be unlikely to delay the execution of the
buy-sell provision by more than a few days. A lawyer for
Chris-Craft, Peter Fishbein, did not return phone calls Thursday
night.
</P>
<P>
   Chris-Craft had argued that Viacom violated a noncompete
provision of the companies' joint venture agreement when it moved
to acquire CBS, a network competitor of UPN. The judge disagreed
and refused to grant an injunction blocking the Viacom-CBS merger
or the enactment of the buy-sell agreement.
</P>
<P>
   After talks about a possible acquisition of Chris-Craft proved
fruitless, Viacom and CBS invoked the buy-sell provision in
February, setting in motion a 45-day deadline for Chris-Craft to
either buy or sell its interest in UPN. Unless the appeals court
grants a delay, Chris-Craft will have to make its decision about
UPN by the close of business on Monday.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
